# Commit & deploy (`c&d`)

When the user says **commit & deploy**, **c&d**, or **ship it**, run this workflow end-to-end without asking unless blocked.

## Steps (in order)

1. `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -3 --oneline` — if nothing to commit, say so and still build + deploy.
2. `npm test && npm run build` — fix failures before committing.
3. Stage only app-relevant changes. **Do not** add `docs/ux-audit/`, `.env*`, or secrets unless the user asks.
4. Commit with a concise HEREDOC message (1–2 sentences, focus on why).
5. `git push origin master` (request approval if the environment blocks protected-branch push).
6. Deploy: `npx wrangler pages deploy dist --project-name ccna-study-tool --branch master --commit-dirty=true`

## Report back

- Commit hash + message (if committed)
- Live URL: https://master.ccna-study-tool.pages.dev
- Note if deploy was skipped (no changes / tests failed)

## Do not

- Force-push, amend, or skip hooks unless the user explicitly asks
- Push or deploy without runnable tests and a successful build
